component = js function that returns jsx, such as App()
components needs to start with Captal Letter

prop = js object that exists inside the argument of a component

ternary operators = condition ? 1st statement : 2nd statement
                    age < 18 ? console.log("Underage") : console.log("Overage")

                    condition && statement
                    isAlive && console.log("Continue")


array:{
forEach
map
filter
reduce
}

callback function = passed as args to another function
                    allows a function to call another function
                    
state = kind like a variable that holds data

component lifecycle =
- mounting (component appears on the website)
- updating (component changes)
- unmounting (component disappears from the website)
We can use the useEffect hook to execute code on those lifecycle
